author: @pandalandalopalis6515
text:
I love Vernon and see where he was going with the caramel popcorn = sticky fingers point, but caramel popcorn is actually the one popcorn that doesn't leave residue on your hands. Unless it's different in Korea, when I have caramel popcorn it's a dried caramel coating and not actively liquid or sticky. It's kind of like a shell and because it's dry, it doesn't leave caramel residue on your fingers. Whereas generally every other type of popcorn will leave some kind of residue on your hands (be it salt, butter, savory, white cheddar, etc.)
Anyway the debate is not meant to be logical hahaha but I'm surprised the caramel team didn't counter with this point

author: @ayuannur9557
text:
Our Logic and Debate Ace, Moon Junhui. 

Fly Carats to the moon
Let Carats play among the stars
Let Carats see what spring is like
On a, Jupiter and Mars


Hopefully it won't be burden for you if ever there's the next debate night. I don't want Jun to feel burden. But also, just like other Carats, I feel so much proud and happy that Jun being polite, well mannered, never mocked other members, showing how he always remembers Carats, applaud or nod when he's in agreement with other member, and asked Wonwoo politely while patiently waiting for his turn to talk. You know, these really shows the quality of someone's personality. So proud for always stan for you! 

Though, I kinda a little bit feeling bad. Especially when other Carats pointed out that sarcastically that Jun only using the "Carat" card. The first one is great, the next one is great too, but feel kinda weak since Jun using the same reasoning again: Carat. 
But screw my high expectations. Knowing Jun being Seventeen Jun always remember Carat is enough for my heart.

author: @beilinyi328
text:
Hi everyone, you all want to know
I'm actually a new CARAT
at first the bias was Minghao (THE 8), but the longer I got to know and look at SEVENTEEN, my bias changed from Minghao to Jun and until now I really like Jun. I tried looking at all of Seventeenâ€™s videos and was definitely looking for Jun. From concert videos, Inside Seventeen, Going Seventeen as well as videos from YouTube. But Iâ€™m a little sad because if youâ€™re all looking for Jun -related videos, the quantity is very little. I also like to find comments from CARAT or Non-Carat about June because since I got to know June. I found him to be a human being who needed to be protected because he was a very good person, indeed many saw him as a quiet person but in fact he was a friendly person and talked a lot. this is because I watched her videos related to Chinese programs or interviews, she was very confident and very happy. Also, I once read from one of the websites or watched a video i.e. member Minghao once said that Jun told him about the difficulty of speaking in Korean, so Jun expressed through deeds. Mingyu also once said that Jun looks quiet but in fact he is a caring person in silence and in fact I can see his concern for his members as well as others. if you all pay close attention, you will all be able to see the thing. But now more and more, he is a little brave and has the confidence to stand out and speak properly with the help of members and he tries to interact with us (CARAT). Actually the main point I want to say is that I feel very happy because this is the first time I see Junâ€™s name a lot in the comment space. because usually when I see any video related to Seventeen, Iâ€™ll look for Junâ€™s name. And I find that very rarely people comment on Jun and there are some videos, there is no Jun's name at all. I feel very sad because many do not see the real Jun. In conclusion, this video is my favorite for now, because just an hour into this video was uploaded already a lot of June names. (there were 60 comments out of 2,749 mentioning Juneâ€™s name).
I am very, very happy. I hope Jun will have high confidence to talk more
as well as I hope you all can see Jun from the other side.
forgive me for not being good at speaking English

I love you all
I love Seventeen
I love JUN


Moonranghae
Junranghae
Huiranghae
